> 	Also, I got some recent details about Kelley Park
> the following Sunday,
> April 7th.  Based of the current situation, it looks
> like it's going to be
> very packed again this year.   A new rule for the
> park, this year, NO CARS
> ON THE GRASS!  This was mandated by Kelley Park, not
> by the Golden Gate
> chapter.  ULP!  That means it will be similar to
> what was seen last year on
> the 'rain/wet grass' plan.  Also, The lower parking
> lot will NOT be used for
> the swap.  This was mandated by the City of San
> Jose, not by the Golden Gate
> chapter.  Another, smaller area in the park is
> planned to be used along with
> some of the (former) car show space.  They are
> working on both of these
> issues and plans may change in a moments
> notice...hopefully for the better.
> My suggestion is to get there early!
> 
> 	More info about Kelley Park can be found at
